From 79f30bd5be2c47ef24530908f970da69d1d8ecc7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Daniel Morandini <daniel.morandini@keepinmind.info>
Date: Wed, 6 May 2026 14:17:14 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] fftools/ffmpeg_demux, avformat/demux: fix copyts MPEG-TS
 rollover
To: ffmpeg-devel@ffmpeg.org

With -copyts, ts_discontinuity_detect() normally disables timestamp
correction. For formats with AVFMT_TS_DISCONT, however, it has a special
case that re-enables correction when adding one timestamp wrap to the
packet DTS makes it close to the expected next DTS.

For MPEG-TS this can be an ordinary 33-bit timestamp wrap, not an input
discontinuity. Accumulating that delta into the demuxer's shared
ts_offset_discont can make different streams receive divergent offsets
after long-running inputs, which can break interleaving and starve one
stream while the other continues.

Keep the per-packet DTS/PTS wrap correction, but do not accumulate the
delta into ts_offset_discont for the copyts wrap path. Log that path only
at debug level, while preserving warning logs and global offset updates for
normal non-copyts discontinuity correction.

A related packet can also arrive with PTS and DTS in adjacent wrap epochs.
If PTS is behind DTS by more than half the timestamp range, move PTS into
the DTS epoch before reporting invalid timestamps.

Reproduced with a generated MPEG-TS pipeline using -copyts and
-mpegts_copyts across the 33-bit timestamp wrap. Validated with both a
near-wrap long-ingest case and a zero-start first-wrap case; both keep
audio and video output continuous and avoid timestamp discontinuity and
invalid timestamp warnings. FATE passes.

Signed-off-by: Daniel Morandini <daniel.morandini@keepinmind.info>
---
Notes for reviewers:

The issue was first observed in a long-running pipeline shaped as:

    generated MPEG-TS -> ffmpeg -copyts -> video filter/transcode
    + AAC transcode -> MPEG-TS stdout

with -mpegts_copyts enabled on both MPEG-TS muxing steps. The input is
synthetic lavfi audio/video, so no external sample file is needed. The
real-time wall clock to reproduce is shortened by letting ffmpeg process
the generated stream as fast as possible.

Two cases were used for validation:

1. Start the generated MPEG-TS around 3 hours before the raw 33-bit
   timestamp wrap, then continue monitoring after the first observed wrap.
   The first raw source wrap itself passes, but without this fix the
   transcoding process later starts reporting timestamp discontinuities
   and one stream starves around the point where a full 33-bit wrap of
   stream time has been ingested (~26.5h logical time, ~175-190s wall time
   in the reproducer).

2. Start timestamps at zero and run through the first 33-bit wrap.

The failure measurement was recent-window PES counts from the output
MPEG-TS. The bad case reaches audio=0 while video continues, together with
visible timestamp discontinuity/invalid timestamp warnings and divergent
per-stream discontinuity offsets. With this patch, both validation cases
keep audio and video PES increasing after wrap, no suspicious timestamp
warnings are emitted, and the observed audio/video PES ratio remains about
1.9x, which is expected for AAC frames at 48 kHz versus 25 fps video.

FATE passes with this patch applied.

 fftools/ffmpeg_demux.c | 5 +++--
 libavformat/demux.c    | 5 +++++
 2 files changed, 8 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/fftools/ffmpeg_demux.c b/fftools/ffmpeg_demux.c
index 04ee2cc2ed..77406b5027 100644
--- a/fftools/ffmpeg_demux.c
+++ b/fftools/ffmpeg_demux.c
@@ -248,8 +248,9 @@ static void ts_discontinuity_detect(Demuxer *d, InputStream *ist,
         if (fmt_is_discont) {
             if (FFABS(delta) > 1LL * dts_delta_threshold * AV_TIME_BASE ||
                 pkt_dts + AV_TIME_BASE/10 < ds->dts) {
-                d->ts_offset_discont -= delta;
-                av_log(ist, AV_LOG_WARNING,
+                if (!copy_ts)
+                    d->ts_offset_discont -= delta;
+                av_log(ist, copy_ts ? AV_LOG_DEBUG : AV_LOG_WARNING,
                        "timestamp discontinuity "
                        "(stream id=%d): %"PRId64", new offset= %"PRId64"\n",
                        ist->st->id, delta, d->ts_offset_discont);
diff --git a/libavformat/demux.c b/libavformat/demux.c
index a1909237f0..e8138ccb23 100644
--- a/libavformat/demux.c
+++ b/libavformat/demux.c
@@ -1461,6 +1461,11 @@ static int read_frame_internal(AVFormatContext *s, AVPacket *pkt)
             sti->need_context_update = 0;
         }
 
+        if (pkt->pts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE && pkt->dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE &&
+            pkt->pts < pkt->dts && st->pts_wrap_bits < 63 &&
+            pkt->dts - (uint64_t)pkt->pts > (1LL << (st->pts_wrap_bits - 1)))
+            pkt->pts = av_sat_add64(pkt->pts, 1LL << st->pts_wrap_bits);
+
         if (pkt->pts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE &&
             pkt->dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE &&
             pkt->pts < pkt->dts) {
-- 
2.53.0

